Gradle Program (Groovy DSL)
Step 1: Create Gradle Project

Open CMD and run:

gradle init --type java-application

Give inputs:

Java version: 17
Project name: groovyProject
Selection: 1
DSL: 2 (Groovy)
Test framework: 1 (JUnit 4)
Generate build using new APIs: no

Step 2: Open build.gradle

Paste this code:

plugins {
    id 'application'
}

application {
    mainClass = 'com.example.AdditionOperation'
}

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.13.2'
}

test {
    outputs.upToDateWhen { false }

    testLogging {
        events "passed", "failed", "skipped"
        exceptionFormat "full"
        showStandardStreams = true
    }
}

Step 3: Open AdditionOperation.java

Path:

src/main/java/com/example/AdditionOperation.java

Paste this code:

package com.example;

public class AdditionOperation {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        double num1 = 5;
        double num2 = 10;

        double sum = num1 + num2;

        System.out.printf("The sum of %.2f and %.2f is %.2f%n", num1, num2, sum);
    }
}

Step 4: Open AdditionOperationTest.java

Path:

src/test/java/com/example/AdditionOperationTest.java

Paste this code:

package com.example;

import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.*;

public class AdditionOperationTest {

    @Test
    public void testAddition() {

        double num1 = 5;
        double num2 = 10;

        double expectedSum = num1 + num2;

        double actualSum = num1 + num2;

        assertEquals(expectedSum, actualSum, 0.01);
    }
}

Step 5: Run Commands
Build Project
gradle build
Run Project
gradle run
Test Project
gradle test
